  "texts": [
    "Collaboration and Organizational DynamicsCollaboration in authoring was mainly described as engaging with others for data questions, feedback on the design, or help with coding.",
    "In some cases, collaboration also occurred at the beginning of the creation process in the form of brainstorming.",
    "Some participants referred to situations where they used co-workers' code pieces to build further and also with later involvement of them for feedback.",
    "However, the act of creating visual structures in authoring was described as an individual process by most.",
    "For example, P5 said \"It is mostly me who makes the visualization, and the developer [runs] the assembly tool."
  ],
